    <node id="1. Post-16 education institutions are placing increased emphasis on improving foundational literacy skills among learners. This can be seen in further education colleges where students may need to retake literacy exams and apprenticeships that incorporate essential skills programs to reach a basic level of literacy.&#10;2. Although some learners may acquire basic qualifications in English or literature, there is often still a gap in their foundational literacy skills. This issue is being addressed by focusing on teaching and approaching children at the appropriate age to ensure they develop these crucial skills.&#10;3. It's essential to continue developing reading skills beyond basic proficiency as it helps learners build higher-level reading skills, comprehension, and inference abilities. This contributes to their overall academic success and prepares them for lifelong learning.&#10;4. The importance of literacy as a top priority is highlighted by Meilyr Rowlands, who notes that it underpins the rest of education. Efforts must continue to prioritize literacy to ensure students can widen the range of things they read and develop their vocabulary at higher levels." />
