    <node id="1. Estyn, the education and training inspectorate for Wales, has been involved with the strategic education delivery group chaired by Professor Dylan Jones from the beginning. Meilyr Rowlands, the Chief Inspector of Schools for Estyn, is a member of this group and its sub-group responsible for some background work.&#10;2. This group is important because it brings together all the strategic educational organizations in one room, allowing them to understand each other's contributions to the education system and clarify their roles.&#10;3. The expected improvements for the work of the middle tier through this group involve building relationships, making connections, and ensuring a clear understanding of each organization's role in the education system. This collaboration should help improve the overall efficiency and effectiveness of the middle tier in Welsh education." />
    <node id=" for how it will improve the work of the middle tier?&#10;Speaker: Meilyr Rowlands&#10;Content: We've been members of that group right from the beginning. I personally am on it and colleagues are on it as well, and I'm a member of the sub-group that does some of the background work for that group as well, and Estyn has given several presentations to that group. I think the group is important. I remember commenting the first time it met that it was welcoming. The rather obvious thing is that you get all the strategic educational organisations together in one room, but it had never been done before, as far as I know. So, it was a really important step forward for that to happen. I'm a very firm believer in making those relationships, building those relationships, so that people understand what each of us contributes to the whole of the education system. We need to have that forum to be able to make sure that we're clear about what each of our roles is.&#10;Speaker: Janet Finch-Saunders AM&#10;Content: Okay, thanks.&#10;Speaker: Lynne Neagle AM&#10;Content: Okay, thank you. We've got some questions now from Dawn Bowden.&#10;Speaker: Dawn Bow" />
