s can lead to long-term academic struggles for these children. They may have difficulty keeping up with their peers in various subjects, which could negatively impact their overall academic performance and prospects.&#10;5. Delayed Development of Higher-Level Skills: Focusing solely on basic literacy skills without addressing foundational gaps can hinder the development of higher-level reading skills, comprehension, and inference abilities. This can limit learners' overall academic success and their preparedness for lifelong learning.&#10;6. Persistent Gender Disparities: There is a specific concern about the impact on boys regarding reading and literacy, as they often remain low in international assessments. Prioritizing literacy and addressing pressing priorities for boys can help narrow this gap and promote gender equity in education.">
