    <edge source="00 points in each of the domains in the 2020-1 cycle for PISA?&#10;&#10;Meilyr Rowlands, the Chief Inspector of Schools for Estyn, mentions that the target of 500 points in each of the domains in the 2020-1 cycle for PISA is somewhat arbitrary. He suggests that, based on Wales' current trajectory and changes such as the new curriculum, improvements in science and mathematics are expected to continue. However, he notes that reading may require additional attention due to its strong correlation with family and community factors. While Estyn has not directly inspected regional consortia since 2017, Meilyr Rowlands believes they have improved their knowledge. He is also optimistic about the impact of GCSE mathematics numeracy on PISA scores. Therefore, while specific progress towards meeting the PISA target is not explicitly stated, there is a generally positive outlook regarding Wales' educational advancements." target="1. Pilot scheme of multi-agency approach: Meilyr Rowlands mentions a pilot scheme to support schools that require greater assistance. This approach involves collaboration between different agencies to provide these schools with the necessary resources and help them cope with the new curriculum.&#10;&#10;2. Focused funding allocation: Janet Finch-Saunders suggests directing additional funding towards schools in need, particularly those struggling with the new curriculum. While Meilyr Rowlands believes the required funding might not be enormous, he acknowledges that these schools do require extra financial support to implement the new curriculum effectively.&#10;&#10;3. Utilizing national resources: The national resource being developed by Claire Morgan aims to provide detailed guidance on self-evaluation and improvement for schools, including secondaries, PRUs, and special schools. This resource can help establish a culture of improvement and reflection within these schools, supporting their efforts to adapt to the new curriculum.&#10;&#10;4. Emphasis on reading proficiency: Since Meilyr Rowlands pointed out that reading might require extra attention due to its strong correlation with family and community factors, it is essential to focus on literacy interventions and strategies in these schools to help students improve their reading skills and meet PISA targets.&#10;&#10;5. Monitoring regional consortia improvement: Although Estyn has not directly inspected regional consortia since 2017, Meilyr Rowlands believes they have shown improvement. Strengthening the monitoring and evaluation of these consortia could help ensure that schools in need receive the necessary support to implement the new curriculum successfully.&#10;&#10;By implementing these efforts, schools requiring significant support can improve their ability to cope with the new curriculum and better serve their students, despite forming a smaller cohort within the education system.">
