    <edge source="The national resource being developed by Claire Morgan is intended to provide schools with detailed guidance on how they can approach not only self-evaluation but also bring about improvement. This resource is seen as having the potential to support schools in developing a culture that focuses on improvement and reflection, involving all staff in the development process. The resource is currently in the pilot stage, involving around 40 schools, with half of them involved in developing the tools and approaches from the start and 22 new schools joining this year. It will include various tools and approaches that schools can use to improve the quality of self-evaluation throughout the school, including primaries, secondaries, PRUs, and special schools. The ultimate goal is to establish a culture within the school that focuses on improvement and reflection, with all staff involved in development." target=" I think that it's very important. It's Claire who has been specifically tasked with that, so I'll ask Claire to speak about it.&#10;Speaker: Claire Morgan&#10;Content: I think working together with the practitioners, the regions and representatives from local authorities is a great opportunity to develop a national approach, because we know across Wales there's some excellent practice, but we know there are schools that struggle to bring about improvement. So, this national resource has the potential to provide schools with detailed guidance on how they can approach not only self-evaluation, but, more importantly, how they can bring about that improvement. So, it will be a resource that develops over time. It's starting—we're piloting currently with around 40 schools. Half of those have been involved in developing the tools and approaches right from the start, and 22 new schools have come on board this year. But we anticipate that there will be lots of tools and approaches within that resource that schools can use to improve the quality of self-evaluation throughout the school, primaries, secondaries, PRUs and special schools. But it will focus on establishing a culture within the school that focuses on improvement, that establishes a reflective culture where all staff are involved in development. So, we're">
