    <edge source="The concerns regarding ERW (Education through Regional Working) stem from the region's progress, or lack thereof, particularly in light of recent developments. These developments include the resignation of the chair of the joint committee, the appointment of a temporary managing director without clear plans for permanency, leadership team members leaving resulting in reduced capacity, and the departure of various staff appointed just last summer.&#10;&#10;Additionally, ERW's budget has not been agreed upon, and key meetings such as executive board and joint committee meetings have been cancelled. These issues have led to significant worries about ERW, prompting plans for a visit next month to all authorities under ERW's jurisdiction. This visit aims to ensure that appropriate school improvement services are in place and to survey schools in the region about the support they receive from their authority or central teams in ERW. The goal is to gauge any potential disadvantages or impacts on schools firsthand.&#10;&#10;There also seems to be a lack of clarity regarding how ERW plans to manage their collective set of services going forward, with a joint committee meeting scheduled for March 19th, after which more information is expected." target="1. A visit is planned to all authorities under ERW's jurisdiction, including regions in south-west and mid Wales, to assess their school improvement services. This visit aims to ensure that appropriate plans are in place for school improvement services and to survey schools about the support they receive from their authority or central teams in ERW.&#10;   &#10;2. The purpose of this visit is to gauge any potential disadvantages or impacts on schools firsthand, as well as to make sure that ERW has a plan for an appropriate school improvement service going forward. This proactive measure will help identify areas where support is needed and allow for the implementation of measures to improve educational quality.&#10;&#10;3. There is a joint committee meeting scheduled for March 19th, after which more information is expected regarding ERW's plans to manage their collective set of services. Stakeholders hope to gain clarity on how ERW will proceed in managing and delivering school improvement services to address the current concerns and challenges.&#10;&#10;4. A detailed link visit will be conducted to understand how ERW authorities are mitigating risks arising from recent developments, such as staff departures and lack of support at higher levels. This follow-up visit will help evaluate the effectiveness of existing measures and identify areas for improvement in school improvement services.">
