    <edge source="Yes, there is a correlation between a lack of support at a higher level and difficulties experienced by some authorities in providing quality education. Meilyr Rowlands, the Chief Inspector of Schools for Estyn, mentioned that out of the nine inspected local authorities so far in the current cycle, three have been identified as causing concern: Pembrokeshire, Powys, and Wrexham. He also noted that a common factor in these inspections is secondary schools, suggesting challenges in this area for several local authorities and the system as a whole.&#10;&#10;When discussing ERW, one of the regions including south-west and mid Wales, Meilyr Rowlands acknowledged that the lack of support at that level might be the reason why some authorities are suffering difficulties. This is especially relevant for two of the inspected authorities in this region.&#10;&#10;The dispute at higher levels may indirectly affect children by impacting the quality of education provided in these local authorities. The concerns about a lack of local capacity to support schools and the absence of collective capacity centrally contribute to the challenges faced by these authorities." target=" like, we were saying consistently that they tended to be too small. What happened in practice was that authorities did come together voluntarily to have joint advisory services. So, you had Cynnal in the north west, you had the Education and School Improvement Service, you had Gwent—so, they naturally did come together in groups, maybe a little bit smaller than the current regions, but they, of their own accord, produced something not very dissimilar to a region.&#10;Speaker: Lynne Neagle AM&#10;Content: Siân, did you have a supplementary?&#10;Speaker: Sian Gwenllian AM&#10;Content: Yes, just on ERW. Does the fact that there is a dispute on the highest level feed down to the school and to the children? Are the children in south-west and mid Wales affected by this? Are standards decreasing in that part of Wales?&#10;Speaker: Meilyr Rowlands&#10;Content: Well, it's difficult to say directly, but we have inspected nine authorities and two of those are in that area, so, the lack of support at that level, as Jassa was saying, may be the reason why those authorities are suffering difficulties.&#10;Speaker: Jassa Scott&#10;">
